         <abstract>
            <p>
               The Maṣḥafa krǝstǝnnā is the service book for the administration of the Sacraments of Christian Initiation. It includes the preparatory rites and the threefold sercive
               of baptism, chrism and Eucharist. Its structure is the same as of the baptismal book of the Coptic Church.
            </p>
              <p> It is sometimes grouped in manuscripts with <title ref="LIT1975Mashaf"/>. 
            </p>
            <p>The long version agrees with the short versions <title ref="LIT3948MashafaKrS"/> until the recitation of the Credo, then there are many added prayers. 
               The Psalms <title ref="LIT2000Mazmur#Ps61"> 61</title> and <title ref="LIT2000Mazmur#Ps113">113, 20-end</title> are absent.
               The ṣawātǝw prayers are more elaborated than in the short recension.</p> <!--Check--> 
